<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Hehe, Yup this works...kind of an abuse of the system, but....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Angus[CC]">Angus[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:47 a.m. 7/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Hehe, Yup this works...kind of an abuse of the system, but....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1287" TARGET=_self>Ya know your gonna die...How not to lose your best item(s).</A> (Vrunak)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>At around level 20 or so you really start coming into magic items on a regular basis, and before long you have 8 or 9 magic items you have on you in use. So you will end up losing something, just not your favorite items. I think this is an aceptable little abuse of the system only becuase the loses are going to be extreme at higher levels anyway. You may as well be allowed to at least try and protect the harder to obtain items. God knows I don't wanna lose Jboots or somthing that takes weeks to get sometimes.

<P>&gt; This is a little stragedy that works for me. When I'm about to
<BR>&gt; go into a fight that is gonna be close or know enemy PKs are
<BR>&gt; about i open up a bag and leave it open on my screen. If things
<BR>&gt; go bad..ie I'm about to die. I pop up my inventory screen and
<BR>&gt; start putting my good pieces of armor and my best weopon in the
<BR>&gt; bag. That way when I die...the killer or whoever walks by can't
<BR>&gt; loot it(ya cant loot a bag). This at least allows you to not
<BR>&gt; lose your best items.
<P>&gt; Vrunak
<BR>&gt; Ogre Warrior
<BR>&gt; Rallos Zek
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
